10 REM FIXED RATE LOAN AMORTIZATION WITH MONTHLY OUTPUT
20 REM INPUT PRINCIPAL ANNUAL PERCENT RATE AND NUMBER OF MONTHS
30 INPUT "PRINCIPAL",P
40 INPUT "ANNUAL RATE",A
50 INPUT "MONTHS",N
60 R=A/1200
70 X=(1+R)^N
80 M=P*R*X/(X-1)
90 B=P
100 T=0
110 Q=0
120 PRINT "PAYMENT",M
130 PRINT "MONTH","INTEREST","PRINCIPAL","BALANCE"
140 FOR I=1 TO N
150 J=B*R
160 K=M-J
170 B=B-K
180 T=T+J
190 Q=Q+K
200 PRINT I,J,K,B
210 NEXT I
220 O=M*N
230 C=O-P
240 PRINT "TOTAL PAID",O
250 PRINT "TOTAL INTEREST",C
260 PRINT "ACCUMULATED INTEREST",T
270 PRINT "ACCUMULATED PRINCIPAL",Q
280 REM RATE IS ENTERED AS AN ANNUAL PERCENT NOT A FRACTION
290 REM THE FORMULA CONVERTS IT TO A MONTHLY FRACTION
300 REM THE PAYMENT STAYS CONSTANT EXCEPT FOR FINAL ROUNDING
310 REM EACH ROW SHOWS MONTH INTEREST PRINCIPAL AND BALANCE
320 REM EARLY PAYMENTS CONTAIN MORE INTEREST THAN PRINCIPAL
330 REM LATER PAYMENTS CONTAIN MORE PRINCIPAL THAN INTEREST
340 REM TOTAL PAID IS THE CONTRACT PAYMENT TIMES MONTH COUNT
350 REM TOTAL INTEREST IS TOTAL PAID MINUS ORIGINAL PRINCIPAL
360 REM ZERO RATE NEEDS THE SPECIAL PAYMENT P DIVIDED BY N
370 END
